The family normally enjoy a riding session at Windsor every Saturday morning, according to the Sunday Express. although this was believed to be the first time this month that they have taken to the saddle.

Lady Louise, the Queen's youngest granddaughter, is said to be confident on horseback, and regularly goes out riding with her grandmother.

The youngster broke her arm in 2012 when she tumbled off a pony at the Berkshire castle while out with her instructor and a groom.

